"<div>\n  <h2>Mushroom and Kale Noodle Bake</h2>\n  <h3>Ingredients:</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>1 package of noodles</li>\n    <li>1 tablespoon olive oil</li>\n    <li>1 onion, chopped</li>\n    <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>\n    <li>8 oz. mushrooms, sliced</li>\n    <li>4 cups kale, chopped</li>\n    <li>1 can diced tomatoes</li>\n    <li>1 cup milk</li>\n    <li>1/2 cup bread crumbs</li>\n    <li>1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese</li>\n    <li>Salt and pepper, to taste</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h3>Instructions:</h3>\n  <ol>\n    <li>Preheat oven to 375Â°F. Grease a baking dish.</li>\n    <li>Cook noodles according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.</li>\n    <li>Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and cook until softened.</li>\n    <li>Add mushrooms and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.</li>\n    <li>Add kale and cook until wilted, about 3 minutes.</li>\n    <li>Add diced tomatoes, milk, salt, and pepper and bring to a simmer.</li>\n    <li>Add cooked noodles and toss to combine.</li>\n    <li>Transfer noodle mixture to the prepared baking dish.</li>\n    <li>In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle over top of noodle mixture.</li>\n    <li>Bake for 20-25 minutes, until bread crumbs are golden brown and crispy.</li>\n  </ol>\n</div>\n\n"